INTRO

* Tesla (2008, 1.x, 65nm, GTX8800, 9800, 280, Tesla 1060)
* Fermi (2010, 1.x, 40nm, GTX480, 460, 580, Tesla 2070)
* Kepler (2012, 3.x, 40/28nm, GTX680, Titan-Z, Tesla-K10, K20, K40, K80, Jetson TK1)
* Maxwell (2014, 5.x, 28nm, GTX 720, 980, Titan-X, Tesla M40, M60, Jetson TX1)
* Pascal (2016, 6.0, 16nm, Tesla GP100, GTX 1080)
features: 3D stacked memory, 16b FP capable

- Jetson ==> embedded
- Tesla ==> HPC
- GTX ==> desktop

GPU STREAMING PROCESSOR COMPONENTS

* GPUs contain multiple SMs - sharing L2 cache & a DRAM controller
* typical SM contents:
- scalar processors (SP: int, fp, compare, convert. contains ALU & FPU)
- double-precision fp unit (DPU: fused multiply/add DP ops. maxwell = 4 DPUs/SM)
- special-function unit (SFU: sin/cos, recip, sqroot, fp multiply)
- register files (RF)
- load/store unit (LSU: memory read/write)

DEVICE MEMORY TYPES

* register files (RF)
* local memory (LM = part of global memory, thread-private)
* shared memory (HM = on-chip scratchpad for inter-SM sharing)
* global memory (GM = off chip DRAM)
* constant memory (CM =
